  "prompt": "What is the salary of systems engineer for freshers in TCS India?",
  "response": "As of the most recent data available (2023), the salary for a **Systems Engineer (fresher)** at **Tata Consultancy Services (TCS)** in India typically ranges from **\u20b93.2 lakhs to \u20b93.6 lakhs per annum**. This includes the base salary and other benefits like provident fund, medical insurance, and travel allowances.\n\n### Key Points:\n1. **Base Salary**: The base salary for a fresher Systems Engineer is usually around **\u20b93.2 lakhs per annum**.\n2. **Location Allowances**: Depending on the city of posting, there might be additional allowances.\n3. **Variable Pay**: Some components of the salary may be variable or performance-based.\n4. **Hike**: After the initial training period, there may be opportunities for salary hikes based on performance.\n\n### Additional Benefits:\n- Health insurance\n- Provident fund (PF)\n- Gratuity\n- Travel allowances\n- Meal coupons\n\nThis salary structure is standard for TCS and may vary slightly based on the specific campus hiring process or agreements. For the most accurate and updated information, it\u2019s best to refer to official TCS communications or recent offer letters from candidates.",
